@dizawish I don't know what is going on now. I just tried the google manipulation code I wrote a long time ago and it fails in the preload script because window.onload never seems to be called or it's called before preload script loads now. This is different behavior to past Electron releases so I'm not really sure. Although I did manage to get it to work by refactoring my preload script a bit. I no longer rely on window.onload but instead use an interval to check the document.readystate and then inject jQuery, change the text in the google search input field and clear the interval. I've tested this against Electron 1.6.10 and 1.7.2 (beta).

